The independent educational centres in Scotland have a career of academic excellence that has continued in 2018 with another set of extraordinary results in the examinations that are reinforced by individual and collective success in the fields of sport, art, music and other community projects.
With more than 30 000 students throughout Scotland, these centres, represented by the Scottish Independent Colleges Council (SCIS) strive to provide the best level of service to students and parents.
Independent colleges are intended to prepare their students to continue their higher education studies, for the career they choose and for the place they occupy as citizens of the world.
As an educational sector that can design and implement an adapted study plan, modern languages remain a popular and desired assignment in the centres.
As Nelson Mandela said, "If you speak to a man in a language he understands, the message reaches his head.
If you speak your language, it will reach your heart."
This is a powerful reminder that, if you want to establish relationships and generate trust with people from other countries, you cannot rely only on English.
If we take into account the recent results of this year's examinations, we can note that the languages are at the top of the classification tables, being the highest approved rates in the independent colleges.
